---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

import ContactCTA from '../components/ContactCTA.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Ibad-ur-Rehman Rashid" description="About Ibad-ur-Rehman Rashid - AI/NLP Researcher">
    <div class="stack gap-20">
        <main class="wrapper about">
            <Hero
                title="About"
                tagline="Discover my background, my research trajectory, and the systems I build."
            />

            <section>
                <h2 class="section-title">Background</h2>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>
                        I am a computer science graduate from Government Postgraduate College Mansehra, specializing in Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Artificial Intelligence architectures. My core focus lies in the intersection of advanced language models and robust system engineering.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        I spend my time exploring and optimizing Large Language Models (LLMs), Transformer architectures, and Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) frameworks. Beyond theoretical research, I am actively involved in developing practical, deployable systems, such as building cross-lingual retrieval benchmarks and designing platforms for collaborative prompt engineering.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        My engineering environment of choice is Linux—specifically Fedora KDE and where I optimize both software stacks and hardware configurations for intensive computational tasks.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="section-title">Research Vision</h2>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>
                        My current research explores the boundaries of semantic reasoning in AI. I recently co-authored research presented at the AbjadNLP workshop (ACL), focusing on structured ontologies and multi-hop reasoning for specialized linguistic domains. 
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Looking forward, I am preparing for advanced graduate studies in the 2027 academic cycle. My goal is to deepen my expertise in cutting-edge fields such as Quantum Natural Language Processing and Neuro-symbolic AI.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="section-title">Core Competencies</h2>
                <div class="content">
                    <ul class="skills-list">
                        <li><strong>AI & NLP:</strong> Large Language Models, Transformers, RAG Architecture, Agentic AI, Cross-Lingual Benchmarking.</li>
                        <li><strong>Development:</strong> SaaS Platform Design, Dashboard Architecture, Collaborative Engineering Frameworks.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>
        </main>

        <ContactCTA />
    </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    .about {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 3.5rem;
    }

    img {
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
        border-radius: 1.5rem;
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    }

    section {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.5rem;
        color: var(--gray-200);
    }

    .section-title {
        grid-column-start: 1;
        font-size: var(--text-xl);
        color: var(--gray-0);
    }

    .content {
        grid-column: 2 / 4;
    }

    .content p {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .skills-list {
        list-style-type: none;
        padding: 0;
    }

    .skills-list li {
        margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
        padding-left: 1rem;
        border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-regular); /* Uses your theme's accent color */
    }

    .skills-list strong {
        color: var(--gray-0);
    }

    @media (min-width: 50em) {
        .about {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 60% 1fr;
        }

        .about > :global(:first-child) {
            grid-column-start: 2;
        }

        section {
            display: contents;
            font-size: var(--text-lg);
        }
    }
</style>